headline: Amgen data ‘muddies’ outlook for Cartesian, says Oppenheimer
summary: Oppenheimer reiterates a Perform rating on Cartesian Therapeutics (RNAC) without a price target following the company’s Q4 report. The company’s Phase 3 trial in myasthenia gravis remains on track to start by mid-year, the analyst tells investors in a research note. The firm thinks the trial has a “decent chance at working,” but does not currently view Descartes-08 as a commercially viable therapy.
